      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "The reason txindex isn't supported together with pruning is because we haven't heard of any use cases for (another) unreliable index. In my expectation, if you have a need to look up arbitrary transactions, you probably need them for the entire chain. Having it work for an ever-changing set of last few blocks is likely more confusing than helpful.\r\n\r\nIf you have a good use case for this, I'm all ears.",
